{"info": {"author": "Daniel Hokka Zakrisson", "author_email": "daniel@hozac.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta"], "description": "# Certbot plugin for completing DNS challenges using bonk\n\nThis is a plugin for [Certbot](https://certbot.eff.org/) that uses\n[bonk's API](https://github.com/dhozac/bonk) to authenticate certificate\nrequests using the dns-01 challenge.\n\n## Usage\n\n1. Install the plugin and certbot: `pip3 install certbot certbot-dns-bonk`\n\n2. Create a bonk.ini file containing your credentials, the URL to your bonk\n   instance, and the group that your user is in to maintain control of the\n   records:\n   ```\n   certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_endpoint=https://SOCRATES/bonk\n   certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_username=USERNAME\n   certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_password=PASSWORD\n   certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_group=GROUP\n   certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_cleanup_action=record\n   ```\n\n   If cleanup_action is record, records will be deleted after each run. If your\n   user lacks permission to create records on its own in the zones, set this to\n   value instead, which will only delete the values it has added.\n\n   Make sure this file is only readable by the user running certbot, typically\n   root.\n\n3. Run `certbot` using the plugin, e.g.\n   ```\n   certbot certonly -a certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk --certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk-credentials /PATH/TO/bonk.ini -d DOMAIN\n   ```\n\n4. Set up automatic renewal as a cron job, e.g.\n   ```\n   certbot renew -q -a certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk --certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk-credentials /PATH/TO/bonk.ini -d DOMAIN\n   ```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/dhozac/certbot-dns-bonk", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "certbot-dns-bonk", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/certbot-dns-bonk/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/certbot-dns-bonk/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/dhozac/certbot-dns-bonk"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/certbot-dns-bonk/0.2.1/", "requires_dist": ["certbot", "requests (>=2.4.2)", "zope.interface"], "requires_python": ">=2.7, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "summary": "Certbot plugin for authentication using bonk", "version": "0.2.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Certbot plugin for completing DNS challenges using bonk</h1>\n<p>This is a plugin for <a href=\"https://certbot.eff.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Certbot</a> that uses\n<a href=\"https://github.com/dhozac/bonk\" rel=\"nofollow\">bonk's API</a> to authenticate certificate\nrequests using the dns-01 challenge.</p>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Install the plugin and certbot: <code>pip3 install certbot certbot-dns-bonk</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Create a bonk.ini file containing your credentials, the URL to your bonk\ninstance, and the group that your user is in to maintain control of the\nrecords:</p>\n<pre><code>certbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_endpoint=https://SOCRATES/bonk\ncertbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_username=USERNAME\ncertbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_password=PASSWORD\ncertbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_group=GROUP\ncertbot_dns_bonk:dns_bonk_cleanup_action=record\n</code></pre>\n<p>If cleanup_action is record, records will be deleted after each run. If your\nuser lacks permission to create records on its own in the zones, set this to\nvalue instead, which will only delete the values it has added.</p>\n<p>Make sure this file is only readable by the user running certbot, typically\nroot.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run <code>certbot</code> using the plugin, e.g.</p>\n<pre><code>certbot certonly -a certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk --certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk-credentials /PATH/TO/bonk.ini -d DOMAIN\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Set up automatic renewal as a cron job, e.g.</p>\n<pre><code>certbot renew -q -a certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk --certbot-dns-bonk:dns-bonk-credentials /PATH/TO/bonk.ini -d DOMAIN\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6864725, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "e8ef0401709b7e58d85a88c8fda9f755", "sha256": "ebccf4818ea8ec21172866ce5d5f48097ca5b9b774166d65118aba5f5f6cb6dc"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "certbot_dns_bonk-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "e8ef0401709b7e58d85a88c8fda9f755", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=2.7, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "size": 8100, "upload_time": "2020-03-16T15:40:36", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-16T15:40:36.930930Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/ce/1f/a594db503d3f056fd13456d05016b0286f7e0a65e7c0fc9476828e94a8c7/certbot_dns_bonk-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "291075289e1400d41f3d5d42500d4f51", "sha256": "1e61f6b8d83d8628cdf4a8cbea95f7d7421055b50e60757d024a44ecd75052c6"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "certbot-dns-bonk-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "291075289e1400d41f3d5d42500d4f51", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=2.7, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*", "size": 3417, "upload_time": "2020-03-16T15:40:39", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-16T15:40:39.403683Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/16/75/0b6af15328095df567ba8842baa1b7e36caa6327122178fd0f9ebb71c778/certbot-dns-bonk-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.1.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ea241d075d6b153f7e5944ce0e093efb", "sha256": "59c547abca3a74e39e98620932459f25ce08d3d92006f80c482d18efb18a6ed6"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "certbot_dns_bonk-0.1.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ea241d075d6b153f7e5944ce0e093efb", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=2.7, !=3.0.*, !=3.1.*, !=3.2.*, !=3.3.*"